Feature: Data Loading # features/01_data_loading.feature:3
  As a GCO application
  I need to load data from various sources
  So that the dashboard displays accurate information
  Scenario: Load scores data                       # features/01_data_loading.feature:8
    Given the data directory exists                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:26
    When I load the scores data                    # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:34
    Then I should get a pandas DataFrame           # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:41
    And the DataFrame should have required columns # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:47

  Scenario: Load events data                   # features/01_data_loading.feature:14
    Given the data directory exists            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:26
    When I load the events data                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:55
    Then events should be a list               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:62
    And each event should have required fields # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:68

  Scenario: Load announcements data                   # features/01_data_loading.feature:20
    Given the data directory exists                   # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:26
    When I load the announcements data                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:77
    Then announcements should be a list               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:84
    And each announcement should have required fields # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:90

  Scenario: Load cup data                # features/01_data_loading.feature:26
    Given the data directory exists      # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:26
    When I load the cup data             # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:99
    Then cup data should be a dictionary # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:106
    And cup data should have draw key    # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:112

  Scenario: Load outing data                 # features/01_data_loading.feature:32
    Given the data directory exists          # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:26
    When I load the outing data              # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:118
    Then outing data should be a dictionary  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:125
    And outing data should have red_team key # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:131

Feature: Data Export/Import # features/02_data_export_import.feature:3
  As an admin user
  I need to export and import application state
  So that I can backup and restore data
  Scenario: Export application state                       # features/02_data_export_import.feature:8
    Given the data is loaded                               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:139
    When I export the app state                            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:149
    Then I should get a dictionary with all data sections  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:155
    And the dictionary should have version and export_date # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:163

  Scenario: Import valid backup            # features/02_data_export_import.feature:14
    Given I have a valid backup JSON       # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:170
    When I import the backup               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:184
    Then all data sections should be saved # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:195

  Scenario: Save backup to file                                  # features/02_data_export_import.feature:19
    Given I have application state                               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:201
    When I save to backup                                        # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:207
    Then a backup file should be created in the backup directory # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:217

Feature: Backup Management # features/03_backup_management.feature:3
  As a system admin
  I need to manage backup files
  So that I can restore previous states
  Scenario: List available backups                     # features/03_backup_management.feature:8
    Given backup files exist in the backup directory   # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:226
    When I list the backups                            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:237
    Then I should get a list of backups sorted by date # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:243

  Scenario: Compute diff between backup and current    # features/03_backup_management.feature:13
    Given I have a backup and current state            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:249
    When I compute the diff                            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:258
    Then I should get a dictionary showing differences # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:264

Feature: Player Management # features/04_player_management.feature:3
  As a league administrator
  I need to manage player information
  So that the league operates correctly
  Scenario: Load player list     # features/04_player_management.feature:8
    Given the club has players   # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:272
    When I load the player list  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:278
    Then I should get 13 players # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:284

  Scenario: Verify team assignments      # features/04_player_management.feature:13
    Given players are assigned to teams  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:290
    When I check team assignments        # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:297
    Then Red Team should have 6 players  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:304
    And Black Team should have 7 players # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:310

Feature: Tournament Management # features/05_tournament_management.feature:3
  As a league administrator
  I need to manage tournament data
  So that tournament results are displayed correctly
  Scenario: Verify league tournaments exist      # features/05_tournament_management.feature:8
    Given tournaments are defined                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:318
    When I check league tournaments              # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:324
    Then there should be at least one tournament # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:330

  Scenario: Verify outing matches exist   # features/05_tournament_management.feature:13
    Given outing matches are defined      # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:336
    When I check outing matches           # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:342
    Then there should be 4 outing matches # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:348

Feature: Data Validation # features/06_data_validation.feature:3
  As a data integrity system
  I need to validate data structures
  So that the application doesn't crash on invalid data
  Scenario: Scores DataFrame structure                                                                                                               # features/06_data_validation.feature:8
    Given scores data is loaded                                                                                                                      # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:356
    When I validate the DataFrame structure                                                                                                          # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:362
    Then it should have required columns: Player, Tournament, Game, Net_Score, Gross_Score, Birdies, Pars, Bogeys, Double_Bogeys, Eagles, Stableford # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:368

  Scenario: Events have required fields            # features/06_data_validation.feature:13
    Given events are loaded                        # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:376
    When I validate an event                       # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:382
    Then it should have: date, name, type, details # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:391

  Scenario: Announcements have required fields                         # features/06_data_validation.feature:18
    Given announcements are loaded                                     # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:407
    When I validate announcement structure                             # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:413
    Then announcement should have id, title, date, author, body fields # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:399

